        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 4 at 5:41PM CDT until August 4 at 6:15PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 541 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 12 miles northeast
of The Intersection Of I-10 And Highway 290, or 18 miles northwest of
Ozona, moving southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
northeastern Crockett County.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
